QuickCode ("we", "our", or "the App") respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your data when you use our application QuickCode â€“ QR & Barcode Generator.

1. Information We Do Not Collect

We do not collect, store, or share any personal information.

The App works completely offline and does not require internet access for generating QR codes or barcodes.

We do not request unnecessary permissions.

2. Information We May Collect

QuickCode may access the following only if you choose to use certain features:

Storage/Media access (optional): to save generated codes as images on your device.

Camera access (optional, only if scanning feature is added in the future): to scan QR codes or barcodes.

These permissions are used locally on your device and the App does not transfer or share any data externally.

3. How We Use Data

All generated codes (QR, Barcode, etc.) are created and processed locally on your device.

We do not send, upload, or store your codes on external servers.

Your data stays 100% private.

4. Third-Party Services

QuickCode does not integrate third-party analytics, tracking, or advertising SDKs.
If in the future we include third-party services, this Privacy Policy will be updated accordingly.

5. Data Security

We are committed to keeping your information safe:

No external storage of personal data.

No background data collection.

No hidden tracking.

6. Childrenâ€™s Privacy

QuickCode does not collect any data and can be safely used by children. However, we recommend supervision if used in educational environments.

7. Changes to This Policy

